      "weather": "showers",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DANCE GAVIN DANCE (1) has not been too far away at either run to date. Freshened up since an even effort over 1183m at Grafton five weeks ago. Finds a soft maiden and if he lives up to the first two performances he should take this out. JOANJETT (2) made it three close seconds in a row when she led but was nailed late over 1120m at Lismore last time out. Might need some luck slotting in from a wide gate with plenty of pace underneath, but on recent form she is the only serious threat to the top pick. GRACEFUL WARRIOR (7) ran a nice race first-up over 1040m at Grafton then weakened badly from the corner when extended to 1181m most recently. Lightly raced four-year-old mare who deserves another chance back at this trip. Debutant PRESTIGE BLUE (4) is a two-year-old thrown in against the older horses. Trialled in good style at Grafton recently and should acquit himself well. Hard to make a case for the other runners.",
